---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Research Training | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Brenkley Doctoral College's modular Research Training programme — standalone CPD or integrated doctoral modules. £1,500 per module. Research methods for professionals.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Research Training</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">Modular CPD &mdash; £1,500 per module</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">Brenkley Doctoral College's Research Training programme provides professional development in research methods for practitioners, whether or not they are undertaking a formal doctoral programme. Each module is a standalone unit of CPD that can also count towards doctoral methods training requirements for enrolled Brenkley Doctoral College researchers.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Who It's For</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Research Skills for Professionals</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Research Training at Brenkley Doctoral College is for professionals who need rigorous research skills but are not necessarily pursuing a full doctoral qualification. You might be a policy professional who needs to conduct evidence reviews. A consultant who wants to strengthen the methodological rigour of client work. An HR leader building internal people research capacity. Or a doctoral student at another institution seeking supplementary methods training.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Modules are also available to Brenkley Doctoral College doctoral researchers as part of their programme methods training — in which case module fees are included in doctoral programme fees and do not carry additional cost.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Delivery</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How Modules Are Delivered</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm"><strong class="text-foreground">Format:</strong> Online, asynchronous with live Q&amp;A sessions. Modules run over four weeks with approximately 8–10 hours of study per week.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm"><strong class="text-foreground">Assessment:</strong> Each module includes an assessed piece of work (typically 2,000–3,000 words) with written feedback from a Brenkley Doctoral College tutor. Pass/fail with tutor feedback. Certificate issued on completion.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <p class="text-muted text-sm"><strong class="text-foreground">Schedule:</strong> Modules run three times per year (January, May, September). Enrolment opens six weeks before module start. Maximum cohort of 15 participants per module.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="section-label mb-3">Available Modules</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">The Module Portfolio</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

        <div class="card">
          <span class="tag tag-training mb-3 inline-block">Foundation</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Research Design</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">An introduction to research design for professional and applied contexts. Covers the relationship between research questions and methodology, the main research paradigms (positivism, interpretivism, critical realism), and the key design choices that shape a rigorous research project.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted"><strong>Pre-requisites:</strong> None. This is a foundation module suitable for all levels.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="tag tag-training mb-3 inline-block">Methods</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Qualitative Research Methods</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">Practical and conceptual coverage of qualitative data collection and analysis. Includes interview design and conduct, focus groups, observation, thematic analysis, IPA, and grounded theory. Particular attention to practitioner-research contexts and insider positionality.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted"><strong>Pre-requisites:</strong> Research Design module or equivalent background.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="tag tag-training mb-3 inline-block">Methods</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Quantitative Research Methods</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">Survey design, sampling, descriptive statistics, and introductory inferential statistics for non-statisticians. Focus on understanding and interpreting quantitative data in management and organisational research contexts. Practical work using accessible analysis tools.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted"><strong>Pre-requisites:</strong> Research Design module or equivalent background. No prior statistics knowledge assumed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="tag tag-training mb-3 inline-block">Methods</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Mixed Methods Research</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">The design and conduct of research combining qualitative and quantitative approaches. Covers the rationale for mixed methods, key designs (sequential, concurrent, embedded), integration strategies, and the methodological challenges of mixed methods in practitioner-research contexts.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted"><strong>Pre-requisites:</strong> Qualitative and Quantitative modules, or demonstrated equivalent knowledge.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="tag tag-training mb-3 inline-block">Writing</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Academic Writing for Professionals</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">Developing the writing skills required for academic and professional research outputs — from the doctoral thesis to policy reports and journal submissions. Covers argument construction, academic register, paragraph structure, and the conventions of research writing across different genres.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted"><strong>Pre-requisites:</strong> None. Suitable for anyone wanting to strengthen their research writing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <span class="tag tag-training mb-3 inline-block">Literature</span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Literature Review and Evidence Synthesis</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-3">Systematic and critical approaches to reviewing academic and professional literature. Covers database searching, reference management, critical appraisal of sources, narrative review, and systematic review approaches. Includes guidance on synthesising evidence from heterogeneous sources.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted"><strong>Pre-requisites:</strong> None. Particularly useful for those early in their research journey.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Build your research capability</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">Whether you are preparing for doctoral study or developing your professional research skills, our modules provide rigorous, accessible, and practical training. Enrolment is now open for the September 2026 cohort.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-primary">Enquire and enrol</a>
        <a href="/fees" class="btn-outline">Fee information</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
